article.headline: Army 64, Lehigh 59
article.story: WEST POINT, N.Y. (AP) -- Jarell Brown had 18 points and Marshall Jackson added 14 to lead Army to a 64-59 win over Lehigh Saturday afternoon. Matt Bell and Cory Sinning each added 11 points for Army (11-7, 1-2 Patriot League). Marquis Hall scored a career-high 21 points and Phil Anderson added 14 points for Lehigh (7-12, 2-1), but the Mountain Hawks could not overcome a 29 percent shooting performance in the first half. In the second half, Army quickly built upon its 31-24 halftime lead, extending to a nine-point bulge with 11:35 to go on a 3-point play by Marcus Nelson. Lehigh closed the gap when Hall hit a free throw. Hall and Anderson then sank a pair of 3-pointers and Hall made another jumper to make it 48-45 in favor of Army with 6:54 remaining. The Black Knights fought back with a pair of 3-pointers, one by Jackson and another by Brown, which made it a nine-point game with 4:39 to go. Lehigh cut it to a three-point game with less than a minute left on the clock, but Army hit its free throws and forced the Mountain Hawks into a number of turnovers and defended shots.
